H. No. 596 / 55 OG No. 36, 7629 (September 7, 1959)

[ REPUBLIC ACT NO. 2472, June 21, 1959 ]

AN ACT CREATING THE BARRIOS OF TONG0DN0N, IRAWAHAN, GIPARAYAN, CALINGNAN, CANUCTAN AND GUIBWANGAN IN THE MUNICIPALITY OF CATUBIG, PROVINCE OF SAMAR.

Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives of the Philippines in Congress assembled:

SECTION 1. The following barrios are hereby created in the Municipality of Catubig, Province of Samar:

Barrio of Tongodnon, consisting of the sitio of Maykabaan;

Barrio of Irawahan, consisting of the sitios of Matadag, Imaljos and Cognonoc;

Barrio of Giparayan, consisting of the sitio of Hialob;

Barrio of Calingnan, consisting of the sitios of Sowa and Guinsorjan;

Barrio of Canuctan, consisting of the sitios of Caloocan, Gibaca-an and Amambucad; and

Barrio of Guibwangan, consisting of the sitio of Canbebre.

SEC. 2. This Act shall take effect upon its approval.

Enacted without executive approval, June 21, 1959.
